# Enforce LF line endings for all text files.
# Critical for SQL migrations: sqlx checksums migration file bytes at compile
# time; if a Windows `core.autocrlf=true` converts LF→CRLF on checkout and the
# resulting CRLF bytes get scp'd to a Linux host, the binary's embedded
# migrations diverge from any previously-applied DB checksums. Keep everything
# LF in the repo and on disk regardless of platform.

* text=auto eol=lf
*.sql text eol=lf
*.rs text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.ts text eol=lf
*.svelte text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf

# Binary files — don't touch.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
*.woff2 binary
*.gguf binary
